tmnxDDMAux2HiAlarm.name: tmnxDDMAux2HiAlarm
tmnxDDMAux2HiAlarm.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux2HiAlarm indicates the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 2 hi-alarm threshold for the XFP.

tmnxDDMAux2Type.name: tmnxDDMAux2Type
tmnxDDMAux2Type.description: The value of tmnxDDMAux2Type indicates the measurement type of the Manufacturer specific Auxiliary 2 information of the XFP: none (0) - not specified. adp-bias-voltage (1) - LSB is 10mV. reserved-2 (2) - reserved for future use. tec-current (3) - LSB is 100uA. laser-temp (4) - degrees Celsius(C). laser-wavelength (5) - LSB is 0.05 nm. voltage-50 (6) - 5.0 supply voltage, LSB=100uV. voltage-33 (7) - 3.3 supply voltage, LSB=100uV. voltage-18 (8) - 1.8 supply voltage, LSB=100uV, voltage-52 (9) - -5.2 supply voltage, LSB=100uV. current-50 (10) - 5.0V supply current, LSB=100uA. reserved-11 (11) - reserved for future use. reserved-12 (12) - reserved for future use. current-33 (13) - 3.3V supply current, LSB=100uA. current-18 (14) - 1.8V supply current, LSB=100uA. current-52 (15) - -5.2V supply current, LSB=100uA.

tmnxDDMFailedThresholds.name: tmnxDDMFailedThresholds
tmnxDDMFailedThresholds.description: The value of tmnxDDMFailedThresholds indicates which objects of the monitored SFF is in a failed or cleared threshold state. A set bit indicates that the specified threshold has been exceeded.

tmnxDDMExternallyCalibrated.name: tmnxDDMExternallyCalibrated
tmnxDDMExternallyCalibrated.description: The value of tmnxDDMExternallyCalibrated indicates whether the SFP was externally calibrated (true) or internally calibrated (false).

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower4.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower4
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower4.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower4 indicates the Rx_PWR(4) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower3.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower3
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower3.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower3 indicates the Rx_PWR(3) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8462 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower2.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower2
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower2.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower2 indicates the Rx_PWR(2) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower1.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower1
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower1.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower1 indicates the Rx_PWR(1) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower0.name: tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower0
tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower0.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalRxPower0 indicates the Rx_PWR(0) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasSlope.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasSlope
tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasSlope.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasSlope indicates the Tx_l(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasOffset.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasOffset
tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasOffset.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTxLaserBiasOffset indicates the Tx_l(Offset) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerSlope.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerSlope
tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerSlope.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerSlope indicates the Tx_PWR(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerOffset.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerOffset
tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerOffset.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTxPowerOffset indicates the Tx_PWR(Offset) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureSlope.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureSlope
tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureSlope.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureSlope indicates the T(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureOffset.name: tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureOffset
tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureOffset.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalTemperatureOffset indicates the T(Offset) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageSlope.name: tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageSlope
tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageSlope.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageSlope indicates the V(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageOffset.name: tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageOffset
tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageOffset.description: The value of tmnxDDMExtCalVoltageOffset indicates the V(Slope) value as specified in Table 3.16 in the SFF Committee Standard's document SFF-8472 Rev 10.2.

tPortAccIngQGrpTableLastChgd.name: tPortAccIngQGrpTableLastChgd
tPortAccIngQGrpTableLastChgd.description: The value of tPortAccIngQGrpTableLastChgd indicates the timestamp of last change to the tPortAccIngQGrpTable.

tmnxBundleMlfrTable.name: tmnxBundleMlfrTable
tmnxBundleMlfrTable.description: The tmnxBundleMlfrTable contains MLFR specific data.

tmnxBundleMlfrEntry.name: tmnxBundleMlfrEntry
tmnxBundleMlfrEntry.description: Each row entry contains data on an MLFR Bundle.

tmnxBundleMlfrBundleId.name: tmnxBundleMlfrBundleId
tmnxBundleMlfrBundleId.description: The value of tmnxBundleMlfrBundleId is the Bundle Identifier sent with each Link Integrity Protocol message for each member of a tmnxBundleBundleID. The object tmnxPortAdminStatus must be set to 'outOfService' to change this value.

tmnxBundleMlfrIngQoSProfId.name: tmnxBundleMlfrIngQoSProfId
tmnxBundleMlfrIngQoSProfId.description: The value of tmnxBundleMlfrIngQoSProfId specifies the ingress QoS profile to be used for the incoming traffic over this MLFR bundle. The value of tmnxBundleMlfrIngQoSProfId of 0 indicates a default QoS profile is used as applicable to given hardware.

tmnxBundleMlfrEgrQoSProfId.name: tmnxBundleMlfrEgrQoSProfId
tmnxBundleMlfrEgrQoSProfId.description: The value of tmnxBundleMlfrEgrQoSProfId specifies the egress QoS profile to be used for the outgoing traffic over this MLFR bundle. The value of tmnxBundleMlfrEgrQoSProfId of 0 indicates a default profile is used as applicable to given hardware.

tmnxBundleMlfrHelloTimer.name: tmnxBundleMlfrHelloTimer
tmnxBundleMlfrHelloTimer.description: The value of tmnxBundleMlfrHelloTimer specifies the rate at which hello messages are sent across a member link.

tmnxBundleMlfrHelloRetryCount.name: tmnxBundleMlfrHelloRetryCount
tmnxBundleMlfrHelloRetryCount.description: The value of tmnxBundleMlfrHelloTimer specifies the number of times to attempt to resend hello messages when the tmnxBundleMlfrAckTimer has expired before taking action.

tmnxBundleMlfrAckTimer.name: tmnxBundleMlfrAckTimer
tmnxBundleMlfrAckTimer.description: The value of tmnxBundleMlfrAckTimer specifies the length of time to wait for acknowledgment of a hello message before declaring the hello message has not been received.

tmnxBundleMlfrLastChanged.name: tmnxBundleMlfrLastChanged
tmnxBundleMlfrLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxBundleMlfrLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management change to this row.

tmnxFrIntfTable.name: tmnxFrIntfTable
tmnxFrIntfTable.description: The tmnxFrIntfTable has an entry for each port/channel in the system that is configured for Frame Relay. It contains Frame Relay configuration parameters.

tmnxFrIntfEntry.name: tmnxFrIntfEntry
tmnxFrIntfEntry.description: The Parameters for a particular FR Interface. Entries cannot be created or deleted via SNMP SET operations. Entries will exist in this table when tmnxPortEncapType is set to frEncap.

tmnxFrIntfFrf12Mode.name: tmnxFrIntfFrf12Mode
tmnxFrIntfFrf12Mode.description: The value of tmnxFrIntfFrf12Mode enables or disables the use of FRF12 headers. This cannot be set to 'enabled' for entries with a tmnxPortBundleNumber set or bundles with a tmnxBundleType of mlfr.

tmnxFrIntfLinkId.name: tmnxFrIntfLinkId
tmnxFrIntfLinkId.description: The value of tmnxFrIntfLinkId is a Link Identifier that is used when this entry is added to a MLFR bundle.

tmnxFrIntfLastChanged.name: tmnxFrIntfLastChanged
tmnxFrIntfLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxFrIntfLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management change to this row.

tmnxFrf12IntfTable.name: tmnxFrf12IntfTable
tmnxFrf12IntfTable.description: The tmnxFrf12IntfTable contains entries for a port/channel that has frf12 mode 'enabled'.

tmnxFrf12IntfEntry.name: tmnxFrf12IntfEntry
tmnxFrf12IntfEntry.description: Each row represents a particular frame-relay interface that has enabled frf12 on a port/channel. Each row in this table is added/removed when frf12 is enabled on a port/channel.

tmnxFrf12IntfFragmentThreshold.name: tmnxFrf12IntfFragmentThreshold
tmnxFrf12IntfFragmentThreshold.description: The value of tmnxFrf12IntfFragmentThreshold specifies the maximum length of a fragment to be transmitted. A value of 0 specifies no fragmentation.

tmnxFrf12IntfEgrQoSProfId.name: tmnxFrf12IntfEgrQoSProfId
tmnxFrf12IntfEgrQoSProfId.description: The value of tmnxFrf12IntfEgrQoSProfId specifies the egress QoS profile to be used for the outgoing traffic over this frf12 frame-relay interface. The value of tmnxFrf12IntfEgrQoSProfId of 0 indicates a default QoS profile is used as applicable to given hardware.

tmnxFrf12IntfLastChanged.name: tmnxFrf12IntfLastChanged
tmnxFrf12IntfLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxFrf12IntfLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management change to this row.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatTable.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatTable
tmnxPortIngQosQStatTable.description: A table that contains ingress QoS queue-group queue port statistics.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatEntry.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatEntry
tmnxPortIngQosQStatEntry.description: Ingress statistics about a specific port's QoS queue-group queue.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatQueueId.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatQueueId
tmnxPortIngQosQStatQueueId.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatQueueId specifies the queue-group queue ID which is used as the fourth index to the table entry.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffHiPrioPkts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffHiPrioPkts
tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffHiPrioPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffHiPrioPkts indicates the number of high priority packets, as determined by the port ingress QoS policy, offered by the Pchip to the Qchip.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdHiPrioPkts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdHiPrioPkts
tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdHiPrioPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdHiPrioPkts indicates the number of high priority packets, as determined by the port ingress QoS policy, dropped by the Qchip due to: MBS exceeded, buffer pool limit exceeded, etc.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffLoPrioPkts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffLoPrioPkts
tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffLoPrioPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffLoPrioPkts indicates the number of low priority packets, as determined by the port ingress QoS policy, offered by the Pchip to the Qchip.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdLoPrioPkts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdLoPrioPkts
tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdLoPrioPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdLoPrioPkts indicates the number of low priority packets, as determined by the port ingress QoS policy, dropped by the Qchip due to: MBS exceeded, buffer pool limit exceeded, etc.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffHiPrioOcts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffHiPrioOcts
tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffHiPrioOcts.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffHiPrioOcts indicates the number of high priority octets, as determined by the port ingress QoS policy, offered by the Pchip to the Qchip.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdHiPrioOcts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdHiPrioOcts
tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdHiPrioOcts.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatDpdHiPrioOcts indicates the number of high priority octets, as determined by the port ingress QoS policy, dropped by the Qchip due to: MBS exceeded, buffer pool limit exceeded, etc.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffLoPrioOcts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatOffLoPrioOcts

tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdInProfPkts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdInProfPkts
tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdInProfPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdInProfPkts indicates the number of in-profile packets (rate below CIR) forwarded by the ingress Qchip.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdOutProfPkts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdOutProfPkts
tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdOutProfPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdOutProfPkts indicates the number of out-of-profile packets (rate above CIR) forwarded by the ingress Qchip.

tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdInProfOcts.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatFwdInProfOcts

tmnxPortIngQosQStatUncolPktsOff.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatUncolPktsOff

tmnxPortIngQosQStatUncolOctsOff.name: tmnxPortIngQosQStatUncolOctsOff
tmnxPortIngQosQStatUncolOctsOff.description: The value of tmnxPortIngQosQStatUncolOctsOff indicates the number of uncolored octets offered to the ingress Qchip.

tmnxPortNetEgrQStatTable.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQStatTable
tmnxPortNetEgrQStatTable.description: Defines the Alcatel-Lucent SROS series network port egress statistics table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of retrieving the traffic statistics for the queue-group queues being used for the ports to forward the network egress traffic.

tmnxPortNetEgrQStatEntry.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQStatEntry
tmnxPortNetEgrQStatEntry.description: Defines an entry in tmnxPortNetEgrQStatTable. Entries are created and deleted by the system depending on the queue policy being used at the specific port. In release 10.0 tPortNetEgrQGrpInstanceId is added as another index before tmnxPortEgrQosQStatQueueId for this tmnxPortNetEgrQStatTable.

tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdInProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdInProfPkts
tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdInProfPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdInProfPkts indicates the number of conforming network egress packets forwarded on this port using this queue-group queue.

tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdOutProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdOutProfPkts
tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdOutProfPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdOutProfPkts indicates the number of exceeding network egress packets forwarded on this port using this queue-group queue.

tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdInProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdInProfOcts
tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdInProfOcts.description: The value of tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdInProfOcts indicates the number of conforming network egress octets forwarded on this port using this queue-group queue.

tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdOutProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdOutProfOcts
tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdOutProfOcts.description: The value of tmnxPortNetEgrQFwdOutProfOcts indicates the number of exceeding network egress octets forwarded on this port using this queue-group queue.

tmnxPortNetEgrQDroInProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQDroInProfPkts
tmnxPortNetEgrQDroInProfPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortNetEgrQDroInProfPkts indicates the number of conforming network egress packets dropped on this port using this queue-group queue.

tmnxPortNetEgrQDroOutProfPkts.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQDroOutProfPkts
tmnxPortNetEgrQDroOutProfPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortNetEgrQDroOutProfPkts indicates the number of exceeding network egress packets dropped on this port using this queue-group queue.

tmnxPortNetEgrQDroInProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQDroInProfOcts

tmnxPortNetEgrQDroOutProfOcts.name: tmnxPortNetEgrQDroOutProfOcts

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatTable.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatTable
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatTable.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatTable contains port egress queue group policer statistics on network side.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatEntry.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatEntry
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatEntry.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatEntry defines an entry in the tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatTable. It represents statistics about a specific QoS egress queue group policer on the specified port.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatQosPolicerId.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatQosPolicerId
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatQosPolicerId.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatQosPolicerId specifies the index of the egress QoS policer queue group on network port.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatMode.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatMode
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatMode.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStatMode indicates the stat mode used by this policer.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPkt.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPkt
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPkt.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPkt indicates the number of in-profile packets (rate below CIR) offered by the egress Pchip.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPktL.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPktL
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPktL.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPktL indicates the lower 32 bits of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPkt.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPktH.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPktH
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPktH.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPktH indicates the upper 32 bits of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStOffInProfPkt.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOct.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOct
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOct.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOct indicates the number of out-of-profile octets discarded by the egress Pchip due to: MBS exceeded, buffer pool limit exceeded, etc.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOctL.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOctL
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOctL.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOctL indicates the lower 32 bits of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOct.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOctH.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOctH
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOctH.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOctH indicates the upper 32 bits of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStDrpOutProfOct.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOff.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOff
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOff.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOff indicates the number of uncolored packets forwarded by the egress Pchip.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOffL.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOffL
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOffL.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOffL indicates the lower 32 bits of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOff.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOffH.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOffH
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOffH.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOffH indicates the upper 32 bits of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolPktOff.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOff.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOff
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOff.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOff indicates the number of uncolored octets forwarded by the egress Pchip.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOffL.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOffL
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOffL.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOffL indicates the lower 32 bits of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOff.

tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOffH.name: tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOffH
tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOffH.description: The value of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOffH indicates the upper 32 bits of tPortNetEgrQGrpPStUncolOctOff.

tmnxPortCemStatsTable.name: tmnxPortCemStatsTable
tmnxPortCemStatsTable.description: A table that contains CEM Port statistics.

tmnxPortCemStatsEntry.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEntry
tmnxPortCemStatsEntry.description: Statistics for a specific CEM Port.

tmnxPortCemStatsReportAlarm.name: tmnxPortCemStatsReportAlarm
tmnxPortCemStatsReportAlarm.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsReportAlarm indicates the type of Circuit EMulation (CEM) alarm currently active on the port. The syntax of this object mirrors that of the CemSapReportAlarm TEXTUAL-CONVENTION. The values may be one of: strayPkts (1)- receiving stray packets. malformedPkts (2)- detecting malformed packets. pktLoss (3)- experiencing packet loss. bfrOverrun (4)- experiencing jitter buffer overrun. bfrUnderrun (5)- experiencing jitter buffer underrun. rmtPktLoss (6)- remote packet loss indication. rmtFault (7)- remote TDM fault indication. rmtRdi (8)- remote RDI indication.

tmnxPortCemStatsIgrForwardedPkts.name: tmnxPortCemStatsIgrForwardedPkts
tmnxPortCemStatsIgrForwardedPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsIgrForwardedPkts indicates the number of packets that were successfully forwarded.

tmnxPortCemStatsIgrDroppedPkts.name: tmnxPortCemStatsIgrDroppedPkts
tmnxPortCemStatsIgrDroppedPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsIgrDroppedPkts indicates the total number of packets that were dropped due to errors.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrForwardedPkts.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrForwardedPkts
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrForwardedPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrForwardedPkts indicates the number of packets that were successfully forwarded.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrDroppedPkts.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrDroppedPkts
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrDroppedPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrDroppedPkts indicates the total number of packets that were dropped due to errors.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMissingPkts.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMissingPkts
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMissingPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMissingPkts indicates the number of missing packets (as detected via control word sequence number gaps).

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrPktsReOrder.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrPktsReOrder
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrPktsReOrder.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrPktsReOrder indicates the number of packets detected out of sequence (via control word sequence number), but successfully re-ordered.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrURun.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrURun
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrURun.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrURun indicates the number of times a packet needed to be played out and the jitter buffer was empty.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrORun.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrORun
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrORun.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrORun indicates the number of times a packet was dropped because it could not fit in the jitter buffer.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMisOrderDrop.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMisOrderDrop
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMisOrderDrop.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMisOrderDrop indicates the number of packets detected out of order (via control word sequence numbers), and could not be re-ordered, or could not be placed in the jitter buffer because it was out of the current window.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMalformedPkts.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMalformedPkts
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMalformedPkts.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMalformedPkts indicates the number of packets detected with unexpected size, or bad headers' stack.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrLBitDrop.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrLBitDrop
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrLBitDrop.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrLBitDrop indicates the number of packets dropped due to the L bit set by the far end.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMultipleDrop.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMultipleDrop
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMultipleDrop.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrMultipleDrop indicates the number of packets dropped due to multiple sequence numbers.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrESs.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrESs
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrESs.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrESs indicates the number of Error Seconds (ESs) encountered. Any malformed packet, seq. error, LOPS and similar are considered as error seconds.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrSESs.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrSESs
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrSESs.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrSESs indicates the number of Severely Error Seconds (SESs) encountered. This is when more than 30 percent of the packets within a one second window are missing.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrUASs.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrUASs
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrUASs.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrUASs indicates the number of Unavailable Seconds (UASs) encountered. Any consecutive ten seconds of SESs are counted as one UAS.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrFailureCounts.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrFailureCounts
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrFailureCounts.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrFailureCounts indicates the number failure events. A failure event begins when the LOPS failure is declared, and ends when the failure is cleared.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrURunCounts.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrURunCounts
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrURunCounts.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrURunCounts indicates the number of times the jitter buffer went into an underrun state.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrORunCounts.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrORunCounts
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrORunCounts.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrORunCounts indicates the number of times the jitter buffer went into an overrun state.

tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrDepth.name: tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrDepth
tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrDepth.description: The value of tmnxPortCemStatsEgrJtrBfrDepth indicates the current packet depth of the jitter buffer.

tmnxBundleMemberMlfrTable.name: tmnxBundleMemberMlfrTable
tmnxBundleMemberMlfrTable.description: The tmnxBundleMemberMlfrTable has an entry for a frame-relay link associated with an MLFR Bundle.

tmnxBundleMemberMlfrEntry.name: tmnxBundleMemberMlfrEntry
tmnxBundleMemberMlfrEntry.description: Each row entry represents an frame-relay link associated with a MLFR Bundle.

tmnxBundleMemberMlfrDownReason.name: tmnxBundleMemberMlfrDownReason
tmnxBundleMemberMlfrDownReason.description: The value of tmnxBundleMemberMlfrDownReason indicates the reason code for marking the MLFR member link of the bundle to down (i.e. tmnxBundleMemberActive will be set to false).

tmnxWaveTrackerTable.name: tmnxWaveTrackerTable
tmnxWaveTrackerTable.description: The tmnxWaveTrackerTable has an entry for each Wavelength Tracker port on each IOM card in each chassis in the TMNX system.

tmnxWaveTrackerEntry.name: tmnxWaveTrackerEntry
tmnxWaveTrackerEntry.description: Each row entry represents a Wave Tracker capable port on a IOM card in a chassis in the system. Entries cannot be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations. The tmnxWaveTrackerEntry contains attributes that are unique to the Wave Tracker capable ports.

tmnxWaveTrackerPowerCtrlEnable.name: tmnxWaveTrackerPowerCtrlEnable
tmnxWaveTrackerPowerCtrlEnable.description: The value of tmnxWaveTrackerPowerCtrlEnable specifies whether or not the Wavelength Tracker Power Control loop that maintains the interface's transmitted optical signal average output power is enabled. tmnxWaveTrackerPowerCtrlEnable is equivalent to 'tnWtEncodePortCapabilityProgrammed' of the 1696-Roadm MIBs.

tmnxWaveTrackerEncodeEnable.name: tmnxWaveTrackerEncodeEnable
tmnxWaveTrackerEncodeEnable.description: the value of tmnxWaveTrackerEncodeEnable specifies whether or not the Wavelength Tracker Encoding of Wave Keys on the interface's transmitted optical signal is enabled. tmnxWaveTrackerEncodeEnable is equivalent to 'tnWaveKeyEncodeTransmitState' of the 1696-Roadm MIBs.

tmnxWaveTrackerInUse.name: tmnxWaveTrackerInUse
tmnxWaveTrackerInUse.description: The value of tmnxWaveTrackerInUse indicates whether or not the Wavelength Tracker feature is in use by the system for services. tmnxWaveTrackerInUse is equivalent to 'tnWtEncodePortCapabilityInUse' of the 1696-Roadm MIBs.

tmnxWaveTrackerTargetPower.name: tmnxWaveTrackerTargetPower
tmnxWaveTrackerTargetPower.description: The value of tmnxWaveTrackerTargetPower specifies the desired average output power of the interface's transmitted optical signal when tmnxWaveTrackerPowerCtrlEnable is set to 'true (1)'. The UNITS millibels (mBm) are units of 0.01 decibel relative to one milliwatt (dBm) or dBm multiplied by 100. The mBm is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: -5.21 dBm is equivalent to -521 mBm.

tmnxWaveTrackerWaveKey2.name: tmnxWaveTrackerWaveKey2
tmnxWaveTrackerWaveKey2.description: the value of tmnxWaveTrackerWaveKey2 specifies the second Wavelength Tracker Key (or Identifier) to be transmitted on the interface's optical signal when tmnxWaveTrackerEncodeEnable is set to 'true (1)'. Refer to the description of tmnxWaveTrackerWaveKey1 for the valid values based on the ITU channel.

tmnxWaveTrackerTrailName.name: tmnxWaveTrackerTrailName
tmnxWaveTrackerTrailName.description: The value of tmnxWaveTrackerTrailName indicates the trail name of the encode point. This trail is usually transmitted in the OTU pm-tti. tmnxWaveTrackerTrailName is equivalent to 'tnWaveKeyEncodeTrailName' of the 1696-Roadm MIBs.

tmnxWaveTrackerCfgAlarms.name: tmnxWaveTrackerCfgAlarms
tmnxWaveTrackerCfgAlarms.description: The value of tmnxWaveTrackerCfgAlarms specifies the alarms that are to be monitored by the Wavelength Tracker interface. If an alarm bit is set, then the corresponding alarm will generate a raise or clear notification when its state changes. An unset bit specifies that the alarm corresponding with the bit will not report on its state transitions.

tmnxWaveTrackerAlarmState.name: tmnxWaveTrackerAlarmState
tmnxWaveTrackerAlarmState.description: The value of tmnxWaveTrackerAlarmState indicates which monitored alarms are raised against the Wavelength Tracker interface.

tmnxWaveTrackerMeasuredPower.name: tmnxWaveTrackerMeasuredPower
tmnxWaveTrackerMeasuredPower.description: tmnxWaveTrackerMeasuredPower indicates the current average output power of the interface's transmitted optical signal. The UNITS mBm are units of 0.01 dBm or dBm multiplied by 100. The mBm is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: -5.21 dBm is equivalent to -521 mBm.

tmnxWaveTrackerMaxAttainablePwr.name: tmnxWaveTrackerMaxAttainablePwr
tmnxWaveTrackerMaxAttainablePwr.description: tmnxWaveTrackerMaxAttainablePwr indicates the maximum average output power of the interface's transmitted optical signal at end of life. The UNITS mBm are units of 0.01 dBm or dBm multiplied by 100. The mBm is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: -5.21 dBm is equivalent to -521 mBm.

tmnxWaveTrackerMinAttainablePwr.name: tmnxWaveTrackerMinAttainablePwr
tmnxWaveTrackerMinAttainablePwr.description: tmnxWaveTrackerMinAttainablePwr indicates the minimum average output power of the interface's transmitted optical signal at end of life. The UNITS mBm are units of 0.01 dBm or dBm multiplied by 100. The mBm is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: -5.21 dBm is equivalent to -521 mBm.

tmnxWaveTrackerUpperPowerMargin.name: tmnxWaveTrackerUpperPowerMargin
tmnxWaveTrackerUpperPowerMargin.description: tmnxWaveTrackerUpperPowerMargin indicates how much the average output power of the interface's transmitted optical signal can be increased. The UNITS millibels (mB) are units of 0.01 dB or dB multiplied by 100. The mB is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: 5.21 dB is equivalent to 521 mB.

tmnxWaveTrackerLowerPowerMargin.name: tmnxWaveTrackerLowerPowerMargin
tmnxWaveTrackerLowerPowerMargin.description: tmnxWaveTrackerLowerPowerMargin indicates how much the average output power of the interface's transmitted optical signal can be decreased. The UNITS mBm are units of 0.01 dB or dB multiplied by 100. The mB is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: 5.21 dB is equivalent to 521 mB.

tPortAccEgrQGrpHMTableLastChgd.name: tPortAccEgrQGrpHMTableLastChgd
tPortAccEgrQGrpHMTableLastChgd.description: The value of tPortAccEgrQGrpHMTableLastChgd indicates the timestamp of last change to the tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchTable.

tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchTable.name: tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchTable
tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchTable.description: The value of tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchTable defines a set of string values optionally used by subscriber management to map subscriber's and subscriber host's policed traffic to a specific egress port queue group.

tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchEntry.name: tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchEntry
tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchEntry.description: The value of tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchEntry defines an entry in the tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchTable. Entries are created/deleted in this table by SNMP sets to tPortAccEgrQGrpHMRowStatus.

tPortAccEgrQGrpHMIntDestId.name: tPortAccEgrQGrpHMIntDestId
tPortAccEgrQGrpHMIntDestId.description: The value of tPortAccEgrQGrpHMIntDestId defines the intermediate destination id to match on.

tPortAccEgrQGrpHMOrgString.name: tPortAccEgrQGrpHMOrgString
tPortAccEgrQGrpHMOrgString.description: The value of tPortAccEgrQGrpHMOrgString defines the organization string to match on. If tPortAccEgrQGrpHMOrgString is the empty string (''), every subscriber with an organization string will not match this entry. If tPortAccEgrQGrpHMOrgString is the wildcard symbol ('*'), every subscriber with an organization string will match this entry, if the tPortAccEgrQGrpHMIntDestId matches. Currently only the empty string ('') is accepted.

tPortAccEgrQGrpHMRowStatus.name: tPortAccEgrQGrpHMRowStatus
tPortAccEgrQGrpHMRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
tPortAccEgrQGrpHMRowStatus.description: The value of tPortAccEgrQGrpHMRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tPortAccEgrQGrpHostMatchTable. The creation of an entry in this table will succeed only if the queue-group being created exist in TIMETRA-QOS-MIB::tQosEgrQGroupTable.

tPortAccEgrQGrpHMLastChgd.name: tPortAccEgrQGrpHMLastChgd
tPortAccEgrQGrpHMLastChgd.description: The value of tPortAccEgrQGrpHMLastChgd indicates the value of sysUpTime when the host match entry was last modified.

tPortAccIngSchedStatTable.name: tPortAccIngSchedStatTable
tPortAccIngSchedStatTable.description: The value of tPortAccIngSchedStatTable defines access Ingress Queue Group related statistics per scheduler.

tPortAccIngSchedStatEntry.name: tPortAccIngSchedStatEntry
tPortAccIngSchedStatEntry.description: The value of tPortAccIngSchedStatEntry defines an entry in the tPortAccIngSchedStatTable. It represents statistics about a specific QoS ingress queue group scheduler on the port specified by tPortAccIngSchedStatName on the access side.

tPortAccIngSchedStatName.name: tPortAccIngSchedStatName
tPortAccIngSchedStatName.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatName indicates the scheduler associated with this queue group on this port.

tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPkts.name: tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPkts
tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPkts.description: The value of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPkts indicates the number of forwarded packets by this port on this queue-group using this scheduler.

tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPktsHi.name: tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPktsHi
tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPktsHi.description: The value of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPktsHi indicates upper 32 bits of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPkts object.

tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPktsLo.name: tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPktsLo
tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPktsLo.description: The value of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPktsLo indicates lower 32 bits of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdPkts object.

tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOcts.name: tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOcts
tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOcts.description: The value of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOcts indicates the number of forwarded octets by this port on this queue-group using this scheduler.

tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOctsHi.name: tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOctsHi
tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOctsHi.description: The value of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOctsHi indicates upper 32 bits of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOcts object.

tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOctsLo.name: tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOctsLo
tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOctsLo.description: The value of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOctsLo indicates lower 32 bits of tPortAccIngSchedStatFwdOcts object.

tPortAccEgrSchedStatTable.name: tPortAccEgrSchedStatTable
tPortAccEgrSchedStatTable.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatTable defines access Egress Queue Group related statistics per scheduler.

tPortAccEgrSchedStatEntry.name: tPortAccEgrSchedStatEntry
tPortAccEgrSchedStatEntry.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatEntry defines an entry in the tPortAccEgrSchedStatTable. It represents statistics about a specific QoS egress queue group scheduler on the port specified by tPortAccEgrSchedStatName on the access side.

tPortAccEgrSchedStatName.name: tPortAccEgrSchedStatName
tPortAccEgrSchedStatName.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatName indicates the scheduler associated with this queue group on this port.

tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPkts.name: tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPkts
tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPkts.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPkts indicates the number of forwarded packets by this port on this queue-group using this scheduler.

tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPktsHi.name: tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPktsHi
tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPktsHi.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPktsHi indicates upper 32 bits of tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPkts object.

tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPktsLo.name: tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPktsLo
tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPktsLo.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPktsLo indicates lower 32 bits of tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdPkts object.

tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOcts.name: tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOcts
tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOcts.description: tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOcts indicates the number of forwarded octets by this port on this queue-group using this scheduler.

tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOctsHi.name: tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOctsHi
tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOctsHi.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOctsHi indicates upper 32 bits of tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOcts object.

tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOctsLo.name: tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOctsLo
tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOctsLo.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOctsLo indicates lower 32 bits of tPortAccEgrSchedStatFwdOcts object.

tPortNetEgrSchedStatTable.name: tPortNetEgrSchedStatTable
tPortNetEgrSchedStatTable.description: The value of tPortNetEgrSchedStatTable defines network Egress Queue Group related statistics per scheduler.

tPortNetEgrSchedStatEntry.name: tPortNetEgrSchedStatEntry
tPortNetEgrSchedStatEntry.description: The value of tPortNetEgrSchedStatEntry defines an entry in the tPortNetEgrSchedStatTable. It represents statistics about a specific QoS egress queue group scheduler on the port specified by tPortNetEgrSchedStatName on the network side.

tPortNetEgrSchedStatName.name: tPortNetEgrSchedStatName
tPortNetEgrSchedStatName.description: The value of tPortAccEgrSchedStatName indicates the scheduler associated with this queue group on this port.

tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPkts.name: tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPkts
tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPkts.description: The value of tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPkts indicates the number of forwarded packets by this port on this queue-group using this scheduler.

tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPktsHi.name: tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPktsHi
tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPktsHi.description: The value of tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPktsHi indicates upper 32 bits of tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPkts object.

tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPktsLo.name: tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPktsLo
tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPktsLo.description: tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPktsLo indicates lower 32 bits of tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdPkts object.

tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOcts.name: tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOcts
tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOcts.description: The value of tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOcts indicates the number of forwarded octets by this port on this queue-group using this scheduler.

tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOctsHi.name: tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOctsHi
tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOctsHi.description: tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOctsHi indicates upper 32 bits of tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOcts object.

tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOctsLo.name: tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOctsLo
tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOctsLo.description: The value of tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOctsLo indicates lower 32 bits of tPortNetEgrSchedStatFwdOcts object.

tPortEgrVPortTableLastChgd.name: tPortEgrVPortTableLastChgd
tPortEgrVPortTableLastChgd.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortTableLastChgd indicates the timestamp of last change to the tPortEgrVPortTable.

tPortEgrVPortTable.name: tPortEgrVPortTable
tPortEgrVPortTable.description: The tPortEgrVPortTable has an entry for each virtual port defined on this port.

tPortEgrVPortEntry.name: tPortEgrVPortEntry
tPortEgrVPortEntry.description: Each row entry represents a virtual port defined on the port for the chassis in the system.

tPortEgrVPortName.name: tPortEgrVPortName
tPortEgrVPortName.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortName is the name of the virtual port on this port.

tPortEgrVPortRowStatus.name: tPortEgrVPortRowStatus
tPortEgrVPortRowStatus.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortRowStatus specifies the row-status of this entry in this table.

tPortEgrVPortLastChanged.name: tPortEgrVPortLastChanged
tPortEgrVPortLastChanged.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortLastChanged indicates the time-stamp of the last change in this entry.

tPortEgrVPortDescr.name: tPortEgrVPortDescr
tPortEgrVPortDescr.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortDescr specifies the description of the virtual port.

tPortEgrVPortSchedPol.name: tPortEgrVPortSchedPol
tPortEgrVPortSchedPol.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortSchedPol specifies the name of the port scheduler policy assigned to this virtual port.

tPortEgrVPortAggRateLimit.name: tPortEgrVPortAggRateLimit
tPortEgrVPortAggRateLimit.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortAggRateLimit specifies the maximum total rate of all subscribers for this virtual port. The value -1 means that there is no limit.

tPortEgrVPortHMTableLastChgd.name: tPortEgrVPortHMTableLastChgd
tPortEgrVPortHMTableLastChgd.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortHMTableLastChgd indicates the timestamp of last change to the tPortEgrVPortHostMatchTable.

tPortEgrVPortHostMatchTable.name: tPortEgrVPortHostMatchTable
tPortEgrVPortHostMatchTable.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortHostMatchTable defines a set of string values optionally used by subscriber management to map subscriber's and subscriber host's queued traffic to a specific egress port virtual port.

tPortEgrVPortHostMatchEntry.name: tPortEgrVPortHostMatchEntry
tPortEgrVPortHostMatchEntry.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortHostMatchEntry defines an entry in the tPortEgrVPortHostMatchTable. Entries are created/deleted in this table by SNMP sets to tPortEgrVPortHMRowStatus.

tPortEgrVPortHMIntDestId.name: tPortEgrVPortHMIntDestId
tPortEgrVPortHMIntDestId.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortHMIntDestId defines the intermediate destination id to match on.

tPortEgrVPortHMOrgString.name: tPortEgrVPortHMOrgString
tPortEgrVPortHMOrgString.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortHMOrgString defines the organization string to match on. If tPortEgrVPortHMOrgString is the empty string (''), every subscriber with an organization string will not match this entry. If tPortEgrVPortHMOrgString is the wildcard symbol ('*'), every subscriber with an organization string will match this entry, if the tPortEgrVPortHMIntDestId matches. Currently only the empty string ('') is accepted.

tPortEgrVPortHMRowStatus.name: tPortEgrVPortHMRowStatus
tPortEgrVPortHMRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
tPortEgrVPortHMRowStatus.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortHMRowStatus allows entries to be created and deleted in the tPortEgrVPortHostMatchTable.

tPortEgrVPortHMLastChgd.name: tPortEgrVPortHMLastChgd
tPortEgrVPortHMLastChgd.description: The value of tPortEgrVPortHMLastChgd indicates the value of sysUpTime when the host match entry was last modified.

tmnxOpticalPortCfgTable.name: tmnxOpticalPortCfgTable
tmnxOpticalPortCfgTable.description: The tmnxOpticalPortCfgTable has an entry for each DWDM Optical port on each IOM card in each chassis in the Alcatel SROS system.

tmnxOpticalPortCfgEntry.name: tmnxOpticalPortCfgEntry
tmnxOpticalPortCfgEntry.description: Each row entry represents an Optical port on a IOM card in a chassis in the system. Entries cannot be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations. The tmnxOpticalPortCfgEntry contains attributes that are unique to the Optical ports.

tmnxOpticalPortAmpCfgAlarms.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpCfgAlarms
tmnxOpticalPortAmpCfgAlarms.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpCfgAlarms specifies the alarms that are monitored by the optical amplifier interface. If an alarm bit is set, then the corresponding alarm will generate a raise or clear notification when its state changes. An unset bit specifies that the alarm corresponding with the bit will not report on its state transitions.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCtrlMode.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCtrlMode
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCtrlMode.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCtrlMode specifies the current operational mode of the tunable dispersion compensation module. When TmnxOpticalTdcmCtrlMode is set to automatic, the dispersion setpoint can be retrieved from tmnxOpticalPortTdcmAutoDisp. When TmnxOpticalTdcmCtrlMode is set to manual, the dispersion setpoint can be configured with tmnxOpticalPortTdcmManCfgDisp.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmManCfgDisp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmManCfgDisp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmManCfgDisp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmManCfgDisp specifies the manually configured dispersion of the tunable dispersion compensation module. This parameter is valid when the tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCtrlMode is manual. Dispersion is expressed in pico-seconds per nano-meter (ps/nm).

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCfgRxChan.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCfgRxChan
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCfgRxChan.description: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCfgRxChan specifies the DWDM ITU channel at which the tunable dispersion compensation module should operate. If a value of zero(0) has been specified, tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPresRxChan will be changed by the system to be equivalent to tmnxPortDwdmLaserChannel. tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCfgRxChan should be set to the same value as tmnxPortDwdmLaserChannel in most cases, but may be set to a different value when the received wavelength is different from the transmitted wavelength.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCfgAlarms.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCfgAlarms
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCfgAlarms.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCfgAlarms specifies the alarms that are monitored by the tunable dispersion compensation module's interface. If an alarm bit is set, then the corresponding alarm will generate a raise or clear notification when its state changes. An unset bit specifies that the alarm corresponding with the bit will not report on its state transitions.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmDispSwpStart.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmDispSwpStart
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmDispSwpStart.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmDispSwpStart specifies the the start value for dispersion sweeping on a tunable dispersion compensation module. Dispersion is expressed in pico-seconds per nano-meter (ps/nm).

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmDispSwpEnd.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmDispSwpEnd
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmDispSwpEnd.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmDispSwpEnd specifies the the end value for dispersion sweeping on a tunable dispersion compensation module. Dispersion is expressed in pico-seconds per nano-meter (ps/nm).

tmnxOpticalPortOperTable.name: tmnxOpticalPortOperTable
tmnxOpticalPortOperTable.description: The tmnxOpticalPortOperTable has an entry for each DWDM Optical port on each IOM card in each chassis in the Alcatel SROS system.

tmnxOpticalPortOperEntry.name: tmnxOpticalPortOperEntry
tmnxOpticalPortOperEntry.description: Each row entry represents an Optical port on a IOM card in a chassis in the system. The tmnxOpticalPortOperEntry contains attributes that are unique to the Optical ports.

tmnxOpticalPortHasRxAmplifier.name: tmnxOpticalPortHasRxAmplifier
tmnxOpticalPortHasRxAmplifier.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortHasRxAmplifier indicates whether or not the port has an optical amplifier on the receive path.

tmnxOpticalPortHasRxTdcm.name: tmnxOpticalPortHasRxTdcm
tmnxOpticalPortHasRxTdcm.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortHasRxTdcm indicates whether or not the port has an optical tunable dispersion compensation module on the receive path.

tmnxOpticalPortAmpPowerIn.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpPowerIn
tmnxOpticalPortAmpPowerIn.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpPowerIn indicates the received average optical power at the input of the optical amplifier. The UNITS millibels (mBm) are units of 0.01 decibel relative to one milliwatt (dBm) or dBm multiplied by 100. The mBm is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: -5.21 dBm is equivalent to -521 mBm.

tmnxOpticalPortAmpGain.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpGain
tmnxOpticalPortAmpGain.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpGain indicates the gain of the optical amplifier. The gain indicates how much the input signal is amplified. The UNITS millibels (mB) are units of 0.01 dB or dB multiplied by 100. The mB is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: 5.21 dB is equivalent to 521 mB.

tmnxOpticalPortAmpPowerOut.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpPowerOut
tmnxOpticalPortAmpPowerOut.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpPowerOut indicates the optical power at the output of the optical amplifier. The UNITS millibels (mBm) are units of 0.01 decibel relative to one milliwatt (dBm) or dBm multiplied by 100. The mBm is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: -5.21 dBm is equivalent to -521 mBm.

tmnxOpticalPortAmpPumpTemp.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpPumpTemp
tmnxOpticalPortAmpPumpTemp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpPumpTemp indicates the current temperature of the optical amplifier's pump in millidegrees Celsius.

tmnxOpticalPortAmpModuleTemp.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpModuleTemp
tmnxOpticalPortAmpModuleTemp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpModuleTemp indicates the current temperature of the optical amplifier module's case in millidegrees Celsius.

tmnxOpticalPortAmpPumpCurrent.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpPumpCurrent
tmnxOpticalPortAmpPumpCurrent.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpPumpCurrent indicates the amount of electical current used by the optical amplifier's pump in microAmperes (uA).

tmnxOpticalPortAmpAlarmState.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpAlarmState
tmnxOpticalPortAmpAlarmState.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpAlarmState indicates which monitored alarms are raised against the optical amplifier's interface.

tmnxOpticalPortAmpSerialNum.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpSerialNum
tmnxOpticalPortAmpSerialNum.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpSerialNum indicates the manufacturing serial number in ASCII characters as read from the optical amplifier module. An empty string indicates the serial number is unspecified. The string is expected to contain printable ASCII characters. Any unprintable ASCII characters read from the module will be filtered out. The string will be NULL terminated.

tmnxOpticalPortAmpCtrlState.name: tmnxOpticalPortAmpCtrlState
tmnxOpticalPortAmpCtrlState.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortAmpCtrlState indicates the state of the control loop that optimizes the receive optical power of to the MSA optics.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPowerIn.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPowerIn
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPowerIn.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPowerIn indicates the received average optical power at the input the tunable dispersion compensation module. The UNITS millibels (mBm) are units of 0.01 decibel relative to one milliwatt (dBm) or dBm multiplied by 100. The mBm is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: -5.21 dBm is equivalent to -521 mBm.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmLoss.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmLoss
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmLoss.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmLoss indicates the optical loss occuring in the tunable dispersion compensation module. The UNITS millibels (mB) are units of 0.01 dB or dB multiplied by 100. The mB is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: 5.21 dB is equivalent to 521 mB.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPowerOut.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPowerOut
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPowerOut.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPowerOut indicates the optical power at the output of tunable dispersion compensation module. The UNITS millibels (mBm) are units of 0.01 decibel relative to one milliwatt (dBm) or dBm multiplied by 100. The mBm is used when integers are required instead of floating point. For example: -5.21 dBm is equivalent to -521 mBm.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd1Temp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd1Temp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd1Temp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd1Temp indicates the current temperature of the tunable dispersion compensation module's first Resistance Temperature Detector (also known as a thermistor). The temperature is in units of millidegrees Celsius.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd2Temp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd2Temp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd2Temp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd2Temp indicates the current temperature of the tunable dispersion compensation module's second Resistance Temperature Detector (also known as a thermistor). The temperature is in units of millidegrees Celsius.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd3Temp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd3Temp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd3Temp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd3Temp indicates the current temperature of the tunable dispersion compensation module's third Resistance Temperature Detector (also known as a thermistor). The temperature is in units of millidegrees Celsius.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd4Temp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd4Temp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd4Temp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmRtd4Temp indicates the current temperature of the tunable dispersion compensation module's fourth Resistance Temperature Detector (also known as a thermistor). The temperature is in units of millidegrees Celsius.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmModuleTemp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmModuleTemp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmModuleTemp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmModuleTemp indicates the current temperature of the tunable dispersion compensation module's case in millidegrees Celsius.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMinDisp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMinDisp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMinDisp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMinDisp indicates the minimum configurable dispersion of the tunable dispersion compensation module. Dispersion is expressed in pico-seconds per nano-meter (ps/nm).

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMaxDisp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMaxDisp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMaxDisp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMaxDisp indicates the maximum configurable dispersion of the tunable dispersion compensation module. Dispersion is expressed in pico-seconds per nano-meter (ps/nm).

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmAutoDisp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmAutoDisp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmAutoDisp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmAutoDisp indicates the currently auto-configured dispersion of the tunable dispersion compensation module. Dispersion is expressed in pico-seconds per nano-meter (ps/nm).

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMeasDisp.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMeasDisp
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMeasDisp.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmMeasDisp indicates the dynamically measured dispersion of the tunable dispersion compensation module. Dispersion is expressed in pico-seconds per nano-meter (ps/nm).

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPresRxChan.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPresRxChan
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPresRxChan.description: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmPresRxChan indicates the DWDM ITU channel at which the tunable dispersion compensation module is operating.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmAlarmState.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmAlarmState
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmAlarmState.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmAlarmState indicates which monitored alarms are raised against the dispersion compensation module's interface.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmSerialNum.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmSerialNum
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmSerialNum.description: The value of tmnxOpticalPortTdcmSerialNum indicates the manufacturing serial number in ASCII characters as read from the tunable dispersion compensation module. An empty string indicates the serial number is unspecified. The string is expected to contain printable ASCII characters. Any unprintable ASCII characters read from the module will be filtered out. The string will be NULL terminated.

tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCtrlState.name: tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCtrlState
tmnxOpticalPortTdcmCtrlState.description: The TmnxOpticalTdcmCtrlState indicates the state of the control loop that optimizes the dispersion by tuning the dispersion compensation module to the set point at which the FEC corrected error rate is the lowest.

tmnxOpticalPortDwdmChannelMin.name: tmnxOpticalPortDwdmChannelMin
tmnxOpticalPortDwdmChannelMin.description: tmnxOpticalPortDwdmChannelMin indicates the minimum DWDM ITU channel supported by a tunable optical interface.

tmnxOpticalPortDwdmChannelMax.name: tmnxOpticalPortDwdmChannelMax
tmnxOpticalPortDwdmChannelMax.description: tmnxOpticalPortDwdmChannelMax indicates the maximum DWDM ITU channel supported by a tunable optical interface.

tmnxOpticalPortLaserTunability.name: tmnxOpticalPortLaserTunability
tmnxOpticalPortLaserTunability.description: tmnxOpticalPortLaserTunability indicates if the optical interface laser is tunable or fixed. Value 'unequipped(0)' indicates that the optical interface is not equipped with a laser.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperTblLastChngd.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperTblLastChngd
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperTblLastChngd.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperTblLastChngd indicates the sysUpTime at the time of the last modification of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperTable.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperTable.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperTable
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperTable.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperTable contains the information of each egress expanded shaper at the port level configured on this system.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperEntry.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperEntry
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperEntry.description: Each row in tmnxPortEgrExpShaperEntry represents a particular egress expanded secondary shaper at the port level specified by tmnxPortEgrExpShaperName.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperName.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperName
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperName.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperName specifies the expanded shaper name on the egress side of this port.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperRowStatus.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperRowStatus
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperRowStatus.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperRowStatus specifies the row-status of this entry in this table.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperRate.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperRate
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperRate.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperRate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit, in kilobits per second, of this egress port expanded secondary shaper as a whole.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass1Rate.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass1Rate
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass1Rate.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass1Rate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit, in kilobits per second, of the Class 1 traffic using this egress port expanded secondary shaper.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass2Rate.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass2Rate
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass2Rate.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass2Rate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit, in kilobits per second, of the Class 2 traffic using this egress port expanded secondary shaper.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass3Rate.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass3Rate
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass3Rate.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass3Rate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit, in kilobits per second, of the Class 3 traffic using this egress port expanded secondary shaper.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass4Rate.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass4Rate
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass4Rate.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass4Rate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit, in kilobits per second, of the Class 4 traffic using this egress port expanded secondary shaper.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass5Rate.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass5Rate
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass5Rate.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass5Rate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit, in kilobits per second, of the Class 5 traffic using this egress port expanded secondary shaper.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass6Rate.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass6Rate
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass6Rate.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass6Rate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit, in kilobits per second, of the Class 6 traffic using this egress port expanded secondary shaper.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass7Rate.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass7Rate
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass7Rate.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass7Rate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit, in kilobits per second, of the Class 7 traffic using this egress port expanded secondary shaper.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass8Rate.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass8Rate
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass8Rate.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass8Rate specifies the explicit maximum frame based bandwidth limit, in kilobits per second, of the Class 8 traffic using this egress port expanded secondary shaper.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLastChanged.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLastChanged
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLastChanged.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLastChanged indicates the value of sysUpTime when the egress expanded shaper entry was last modified.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBrstMaxCls.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBrstMaxCls
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBrstMaxCls.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBrstMaxCls specifies which class should use the low priority burst threshold. All classes starting from 1, up to and including that specified by tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBrstMaxCls use the low priority burst threshold. All classes greater than the value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBrstMaxCls up to and including class 8 use the high priority burst threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass1Thresh.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass1Thresh
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass1Thresh.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass1Thresh specifies the monitoring non-conformance burst threshold for the exp-secondary-shaper class-1. When set to default value '-1', the system will adopt a suitable default setting for this threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass2Thresh.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass2Thresh
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass2Thresh.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass2Thresh specifies the monitoring non-conformance burst threshold for the exp-secondary-shaper class-2. When set to default value '-1', the system will adopt a suitable default setting for this threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass3Thresh.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass3Thresh
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass3Thresh.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass3Thresh specifies the monitoring non-conformance burst threshold for the exp-secondary-shaper class-3. When set to default value '-1', the system will adopt a suitable default setting for this threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass4Thresh.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass4Thresh
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass4Thresh.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass4Thresh specifies the monitoring non-conformance burst threshold for the exp-secondary-shaper class-4. When set to default value '-1', the system will adopt a suitable default setting for this threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass5Thresh.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass5Thresh
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass5Thresh.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass5Thresh specifies the monitoring non-conformance burst threshold for the exp-secondary-shaper class-5. When set to default value '-1', the system will adopt a suitable default setting for this threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass6Thresh.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass6Thresh
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass6Thresh.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass6Thresh specifies the monitoring non-conformance burst threshold for the exp-secondary-shaper class-6. When set to default value '-1', the system will adopt a suitable default setting for this threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass7Thresh.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass7Thresh
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass7Thresh.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass7Thresh specifies the monitoring non-conformance burst threshold for the exp-secondary-shaper class-7. When set to default value '-1', the system will adopt a suitable default setting for this threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass8Thresh.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass8Thresh
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass8Thresh.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperClass8Thresh specifies the monitoring non-conformance burst threshold for the exp-secondary-shaper class-8. When set to default value '-1', the system will adopt a suitable default setting for this threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperThresh.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperThresh
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperThresh.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperThresh specifies the monitoring non-conformance burst threshold for the aggregate exp-secondary-shaper. When set to default value '-1', the system will adopt a suitable default setting for this threshold.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBurstLimit.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBurstLimit
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBurstLimit.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperLoBurstLimit specifies the number of bytes to be used as the low burst threshold for the aggregate rate of the classes pertaining to the low burst threshold in the expanded secondary shaper.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperHiBurstInc.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperHiBurstInc
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperHiBurstInc.description: The tmnxPortEgrExpShaperHiBurstInc specifies the incremental number of bytes above the low burst limit to be used as the high burst threshold for the aggregate rate of the classes pertaining to the high burst threshold in the expanded secondary shaper. When set to the default value '-1', the system will default to a value of '4000' bytes.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl1BrstLimit.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl1BrstLimit
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl1BrstLimit.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl1BrstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the class.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl2BrstLimit.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl2BrstLimit
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl2BrstLimit.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl2BrstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the class.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl3BrstLimit.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl3BrstLimit
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl3BrstLimit.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl3BrstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the class.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl4BrstLimit.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl4BrstLimit
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl4BrstLimit.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl4BrstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the class.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl5BrstLimit.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl5BrstLimit
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl5BrstLimit.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl5BrstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the class.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl6BrstLimit.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl6BrstLimit
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl6BrstLimit.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl6BrstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the class.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl7BrstLimit.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl7BrstLimit
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl7BrstLimit.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl7BrstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the class.

tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl8BrstLimit.name: tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl8BrstLimit
tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl8BrstLimit.description: The value of tmnxPortEgrExpShaperCl8BrstLimit specifies the explicit shaping burst size of the class.

tPortEgrExpShaperStatsTable.name: tPortEgrExpShaperStatsTable
tPortEgrExpShaperStatsTable.description: The tPortEgrExpShaperStatsTable contains the statistics of each egress expanded shaper at the port level configured on this system. Most objects are represented in 64 bit. 32-bit version of the objects are available in tPortEgrExpShaperStatsHLTable.

tPortEgrExpShaperStatsEntry.name: tPortEgrExpShaperStatsEntry
tPortEgrExpShaperStatsEntry.description: Each row in tPortEgrExpShaperStatsEntry represents a particular egress expanded secondary shaper statistics at the port level specified by tmnxPortEgrExpShaperName.

tPortEgrExpShaperStLstClrdTime.name: tPortEgrExpShaperStLstClrdTime
tPortEgrExpShaperStLstClrdTime.description: The value of tPortEgrExpShaperStLstClrdTime indicates the sysUpTime when the counters in this table were last cleared.

tPortEgrExpShaperCls1StFwdPkts.name: tPortEgrExpShaperCls1StFwdPkts
tPortEgrExpShaperCls1StFwdPkts.description: The value of tPortEgrExpShaperCls1StFwdPkts indicates the number of packets forwarded by the class '1' egress expanded shaper.

tPortEgrExpShaperCls1StFwdOcts.name: tPortEgrExpShaperCls1StFwdOcts
tPortEgrExpShaperCls1StFwdOcts.description: The value of tPortEgrExpShaperCls1StFwdOcts indicates the number of octets forwarded by the class '1' egress expanded shaper.
